name: YoungKaiser
about:
I'm just a noble casual. Nothing more. Nothing less. 

I have a soft spot for Mecha.  And I generally like any good show that doesn't give my intelligence the middle finger. You can probably assume these are the kinds of shows I hate. Any show that does well with what it's trying to do i will always appreciate. I have been a fan of the medium since around 2011 and have enjoyed it ever since. You can thank Toonami for that. 

Here's my rating system. Now, don't see this as me putting shows in numerical values cause works are more complex than that at times, especially when evaluating them. There's a large spectrum of 5's and 6's and so on. Although the higher the scores get, the more narrow that spectrum becomes, as some of the best works are very well defined in their brilliance(plus there are less brilliant shows than shitty ones). This is for convenience's sake, not an end-all-be-all evaluation:
10= This implies perfection and works aren't perfect. Therefore, Non-existent
9= Masterpiece
8= Magnificient
7= Solid like Z alloy
6= Alright/fine
5= ok/mediocre
4= Below average/dumb
3
2
1= Death
0= Proof of the absence of God (only one show i know fits this description)

name: TopicalTreeman
about: Click is simply the worst film I have ever seen by a behemoth-sized margin. The amount of hate and animosity I harbor toward that film is unrivaled. Adam Sandler is like a Super-Sour Ball, sweet on the inside, tart and tawdy on the outside. Alright, let me brief you about this blockbuster flick: A guy who is down on his luck go to Bed Bath and Beyond, there he goes to the "way beyond" section of the store where he meets the creator of the universal remote (played by Christopher Walken). This is a remote control not just for electronics, but for everyday life. With this remote, one could mute sound entirely, skip a part of his life - such as let's say you are in high school, every time it was a test, the remote would skip it for you. How it skipped it, I am not saying. All in all it is about one lucky dude who found a very powerful remote (he got it for FREE). So, don't get this film, you will be disappointed. That is, if you like Adam Sandler, or if you just like comedy for comedy's sakes! Now, Bruce Almighty, that is an excellent film, one of the best, if not THE best ever made. Jim Carrey is like a bundle of Jumbo-Sized Whitman's Sampler; he has a lot of different things to offer, but you know you'll get something good. Bruce Almighty explores heavy and deep themes of suicide, depression, and genocide, including God leaving on a vacation during the Dark Ages. Bruce literally causes a world-level threat by pulling the moon toward the Earth, which would have surpassed the Roche limit, causing catastrophic death and destruction, like in Super Mario Odyssey (THANKS MATPAT). If Click is a kick in my face, then Bruce Almighty is a makeout session, because it is SO GOOD, and Bruce got his powers for FREE. Watch the movie if you like comedies, or just pleasure in general, or movies. You WILL like this movie. Just go watch it, the Godfather sucks.

name: BluefireF5ran
about:
Hola gente, soy __Bluefire__. He visto 500+ obras del mundo manga/anime incluyendo LN, Manhua, Manhwa etc.
Voy a ser claro, tengo un criterio muy exigente a la hora de evaluar una obra, si esperáis que le ponga un 9 a vuestra serie favorita podéis buscar otro perfil de Anilist.


img220(https://images7.alphacoders.com/109/1094164.png)


Las valoro en 6 categorías distintas por lo que la nota que veréis será la media de todas:
- __Historia__: Introducción, desarrollo y desenlace de la obra, se valoran positivamente buenas decisiones argumentales y giros de guion, también se pueden obtener o perder puntos mediante "decisiones de riesgo" en la trama. (Matar a un protagonista, convertirlo en villano, hacer que el villano cobre más importancia que el protagonista, etc.). Destacamos grandes tramas como _Bastard_ o _Monster_.

    img220(https://cdn.storyboardthat.com/site-images/articles/plot-diagram.png)


- __Personajes__: Dentro de esta categoría se valoran tres cosas principales:
1º Construcción y creación de personajes: Se valoran mejor personajes redondos y con identidad propia, no clichés de otras 100 series.
2º Evolución y desarrollo de personajes: Se valora más una evolución psicológica y física, no solo una evolución en los poderes del personaje. ~~Os hablo a vosotros Shounen de pelea.~~
3º Naturalidad. Se valora la naturalidad y realismo de los personajes, se agradece la ausencia de personajes como ideales, evoluciones artificiales porque la trama lo requiera entre otros.
En esta categoría destacamos obras como _The Beginning After The End_ y _The Girl From The Random Chatting_.
  img220(https://i1.wp.com/danielle-adams.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/character-development.png?fit=777%2C341&ssl=1)

- __Medio__: Aquí se valora cuanto aprovecha el formato en el que está la obra, en un anime se valora la banda sonora, animación y dibujo, doblaje, etc. 
En un manga se centraría mas en el trazo de las escenas y la regularidad de calidad en las mismas o en desarrollar un estilo de dibujo único y propio, también se valoran gratamente decisiones "out of the box".
Como ejemplo tenemos las canciones en manhwas como GUL o DICE, ruptura de la 4º pared en Omniscient reader o el empleo de los frames en Konosuba. ~~Detalles que importan.~~
Destacamos el empleo de las cámaras en _Monogatari Series_, _Solo Leveling_ y la obra que mas abusa de esta categoría, _Berserk_.
img220(https://as.com/meristation/imagenes/2021/05/20/noticias/1621497340_508242_1621497488_sumario_normal.jpg)

- __Mensaje__: Aquí se valoran mensajes, enseñanzas y lecciones de vida que recordamos todos tiempo después tras ver un anime, cosas que traspasan la pantalla y llegan a la persona. 
Se valora positivamente el empleo de realidades y mensajes para apoyar la trama. (Ej. One Punch Man: No es divertido jugar con trucos.) También encontramos hechos que provoquen un cambio o una reflexión por parte del espectador (Ej. Cuando haces simpatizar al espectador con el villano).
Destacamos _Bastard_, _Fire Punch_ y _Mob Pycho 100_.

 img220(https://i2.wp.com/maryfrancesflood.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/truth-and-perspective.jpg?fit=1200%2C900&ssl=1)


- __Entorno__: Se valora la construcción de mundo de la obra, tanto espacio-tiempo ~~escenarios y transiciones temporales realizadas de forma natural~~ como que ese mundo creado esté vivo. Esa buena construcción de mundo proporciona un mayor nivel de inmersión a la obra.
Destacamos _The Horizon_ y _One Piece_ como maximos representantes de esta categoría.


 img220(https://karenmarcescorner.files.wordpress.com/2018/04/medieval_town_by_shutupandwhisper-d6q07yv.jpg?w=748&h=508)

- __Emociones__: Se valoran emociones fuertes, obras que cambian de ritmo y funcionan, que te hacen llorar a lágrima viva, que te hacen levantarte y gritar, que te generan terror y angustia etc.
Destacamos _Fullmetal Alchemist_,  _The Horizon_ y _Girls of The Wild_.

 img220(https://i.pinimg.com/originals/f9/7b/8c/f97b8c7512b5b29f12800850183a2599.gif)

Me gusta la transparencia así que pondre en los comentarios de las obras las notas en el orden que están estas categorías, además, las obras que poseen los mismos protagonistas las valoro en bloque, por lo que obras como My Hero Academia, Monogatari o SNK tienen la __misma nota__ en TODAS sus temporadas. Me parece lo justo votarlas como un FMA o One Piece en vez de votar parte a parte.

Recomendaciones fuera de ANILIST:
- The Beginning After The End: Quien no conoce a dios a cualquier santo le reza y si no has leido esta serie deberías ponerte ahora RIGHT NOW!!!!
- Hooky: La serie basada en Harry Potter mejor que el propio Harry Potter
- UnORDINARY: Una serie de súper poderes como MHA que lo hace mejor que el propio MHA, peores peleas a nivel de estilo (sobre todo comparándolo con el manga de MHA) pero tiene mucho mejores personajes, más naturales y menos idealistas. 



__TL;DR__: Espero que disfrutes en mi perfil y recuerda que siempre estoy abierto al feedback, tanto positivo como si quieres hatearme por ponerle un 4 a tu serie favorita.
Lo importante es que DISFRUTES con este maravilloso mundo de la ficción asiática.

name: ioctan
about:
Most of my notes should warn ahead of time about spoilers, but some old ones might not, so beware.

For simplicity's sake, I use a 20 points interval for my ratings (0.5 intervals), and my scores don't line up perfectly with how much I enjoyed them, but I can't claim to be objective either, but if it's under 5 I probably regret having spent time on it to some degree.  And if I scored something, odds are I left some notes about it.

While I try to take into account plot mishaps, the way exposition is done, characterization, pace, ending, etc. The way I perceive them, and how much importance I give each of them for a particular series, is essentially up in the air. I'm not going to judge a bad ending on an action series as harshly as I would in a mystery manga, for example, and if the author frames their manga as something silly from the get-go I'm not going to mind "convenient" plot developments as much.

I also might take the age of the manga into account, I can cut old manga some slack in the art and paneling department (though I tend to not judge art harshly anyway), as well as not minding tropes as much given that they wouldn't have been that overused at the time they were made compared to the present.

While it's a factor, enjoyment doesn't directly determine the score, so just because something has a higher score than something else it doesn't mean I liked it more, specially if they are different genres.

I also have an affinity for delinquent manga and  I tend to dislike romance and ecchi series, and that's probably going to have an effect on my average score in said series.

Having said all this, I'm not going to pretend my scores are "objective", I think there's no way to judge media "objectively" - different people might disagree on what's an issue, and how important specific issues are for the story.
